On Aug 29, 2005, at 7:12 AM, Clayton Polizzi wrote:

> So if I do a compression check and it comes out to spec, can I  
> assume the internal stuff is ok and will last for many miles?

If the compression is ok, the engine sounds good and oil pressure is  
good you just probably just need to replace the heads. Engine mileage  
is another indicator.

> What other things should I check for with the heads off?  Any  
> articles out there concerning the specifics of changing the heads?

You need to make sure your exhaust seals to the heads properly:

http://www.ratwell.com/technical/Exhaust.html

On Aug 29, 2005, at 7:45 AM, Don Tuleja wrote:

> While you have everything apart, you could replace your pistons and
> cylinders too. And go bigger for not a huge amount of $$.

As you increase bore size, you also increase the heat produced. Just  
keep that in mind...

